Nigerian singer, Innocent Idibia, popularly known as 2Baba or Tuface, has visited the gravesite of the late singer, Olanrewaju Fasasi aka Sound Sultan. He revealed this on Monday via his Instagram page, as he was accompanied by two other friends to pay his respect and tribute to the late singer. Idibia wrote, “Went to pay my respect to my brother Sound Sultan. With my brothers @emmaugolee @amfrankiej @blackahrank. -Advertisement- “July 11, world Sultan day. Blessed #grateful #warrior. We miss you my dear friend @soundsultan. Olanrewaju Fasasi. Bless up.” Recall that Sound Sultan died July 11, 2021, at the age of 44 as a result of complications from battling Angioimmunoblastic T-Cell Lymphoma.